review_blob: Keg at CBC Clerkenwell.It pours near black, thick, with a nice brown head. Nose of plum and alcohol, with some chocolate, liquorice and some smokiness. It feels rich and creamy, with pleasant carbonation. Taste of plums and plum wine, some coffee and chocolate and a very pleasant, mild smokiness. A really great imperial stout! I want another one, as long as I can get home.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Cask at CBC Clerkenwell.It pours clear amber with a thin head quickly dissipating. The aroma is mild, orange with some spice. The taste is ginger and orange, followed by grass and some clove. Very light carbonation, a gentle tingling on the tongue. It is strangely both warming and refreshing. Not a beer I would drink every day, but I am enjoying it.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Cloudy, hazy, golden colour, with a thin head. Jasmin, aroma from the tea. You can certainly taste the green tea as well as jasmin, orange, peach. Great bitter finish, which nicely contrast and complement the fruitiness. Gentle carbonation. This a strange beer, but it"s refreshing and I rather like it.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Chocolate brown with a thin but persistent head. Mildly carbonated, medium bodied and creamy. Aroma of coffee liquor come through, with some coffee and cherry. Chocolate, coffee note come through with a bit of morello cherry. A rather good beer!-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

A decent been, but nothing special, brownish, with a thin, off white head. Aromas of pine and earth that come though the taste. Slightly carbonated and light. Decent, nothing special.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Full of tropical fruit, tangerine and concord grape. The aroma is strong and beautiful. The appearance is golden and clear. A lovely beer-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Lovely aroma, with a nice mango nose. Notes of mango and lychee, with a hint of grass in the taste. Complex hops. Beautiful hazy golden appearance. Gentle carbonation. Lovely-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
Lovely coffee aroma, with some chocolate/vanilla notes, hints of smokiness.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone
